verbs.description: upraise (third-person singular simple present upraises, present participle upraising, simple past and past participle upraised)

entries.meaning: (archaic) To raise something up; to elevate.
examples: So fell those two in spight of both their prydes, / But Scudamour himselfe did soone vprayse, / And mounting light his foe for lying long vpbrayes.

entries.meaning: (archaic) To move something upright; to erect.
